el, J., Michaelson, G., Welker, J.M., Oberbauer, S.F., Liston, G.E., Winter biological processes could help convert arctic tundra to shrubland (2005) BioScience, 55, pp. 17-26; Swets, D.L., Reed, B.C., Rowland, J.D., Marko, S.E., A weighted least-squares approach to temporal NDVI smoothing (1999) Proceedings of the 1999 ASPRS annual conference, from image to information, Portland, Oregon, May 17-21, 1999, , American Society for Photogrammetry and Remote Sensing, Bethesda, Maryland [CD-ROM]; Townshend, J.R.G., Justice, C.O., Towards operational monitoring of terrestrial systems by moderate resolution remote sensing (2002) Remote Sensing of Environment, 83, pp. 351-359; VanDijk, A., Callis, S.L., Sakamoto, C.M., Decker, W.L., Smoothing vegetation index profiles: An alternative method for reducing radiometric disturbance in NOAA/AVHRR data (1987) Photogrammetric Engineering and Remote Sensing, 53, pp. 1059-1067; van Leeuwen, W.J.D., Huete, A.R., Laing, T.W., MODIS vegetation index compositing approach: A prototype with AVHRR data (1999) Remote Sensing of Environment, 69, pp. 264-280; Viovy, N., Arino, O., Belward, A.S., The best index slope extraction: A method for reducing noise in NDVI time series (1992) International Journal of Remote Sensing, 13, pp. 1585-1590; White, M.A., Thornton, P.E., Running, S.W., A continental phenology model for monitoring vegetation responses to interannual climatic variability (1997) Global Biogeochemical Cycles, 11, pp. 217-234; Zhang, X.Y., Friedl, M.A., Schaaf, C.B., Strahler, A.H., Hodges, J.C.F., Gao, F., Monitoring vegetation phenology using MODIS (2003) Remote Sensing of Environment, 84, pp. 471-475; Zhang, X., Harvey, K.D., Hogg, W.D., Yuzyk, T.R., Trends in Canadian streamflow (2001) Water Resources Research, 37, pp. 987-998","Reed, B.; U.S. Geological Survey (USGS), Reston, VA 20191, United States; email: reed@usgs.gov",,,,,,,,00344257,,RSEEA,,"English","Remote Sens. Environ.",Article,Scopus,2-s2.0-67349087939
